{"id":81767,"title":"Prevention of dental disease versus surgical treatment.","abstract":"The members of the Minnesota legislature have debated methods by which access to dental care and treatment of dental disease can be improved at a cost lower than that of present delivery systems. This review sheds light on some significant aspects of what the dental profession has learned over the last century that has proven significantly beneficial to the overall health of the American populace. Recommendations are made in the use of cost-effective dental public health interventions that could be used to provide better access and improved dental health at lower cost.","date":"2014-05-20","categories":"Stomatognathic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24839794","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.813916,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Public health","weight":0.787886,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_health"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.781843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Dentistry","weight":0.709797,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dentistry"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.592698,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Minnesota","weight":0.558091,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minnesota"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.503506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Oral hygiene","weight":0.329832,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oral_hygiene"},{"name":"Profession","weight":0.322557,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Profession"},{"name":"United States","weight":0.281268,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States"},{"name":"Dental disease","weight":0.141573,"wikipedia_article":"h